name: Loom
description:
A juvenile Yellow Garden Spider rests during a light rain, having carefully woven its web. The spider looms, clinging to droplet covered strands, bracing against the falling rain. (Argiope aurantia)

2018. Nikon D60, 55-200mm Lens.

Photographed in situ, without the use of artificial lighting or staging. Photoshop only used for resizing.

1024x685 300dpi jpeg
